  "prompt": "How does coffee help with headaches?",
  "response": "Coffee can help with headaches in several ways:\n\n1. Caffeine reduces inflammation\n- Constricts blood vessels\n- Can help alleviate certain types of headaches\n\n2. Pain relief mechanism\n- Helps block pain receptors\n- Often combined with pain medications to increase effectiveness\n\n3. Dehydration relief\n- Provides hydration (though in moderation)\n- Can help counteract headaches caused by mild dehydration\n\n4. Increases medication absorption\n- Can enhance the absorption of pain relievers\n- Makes some over-the-counter headache medications more effective\n\n5. Potential migraine relief\n- Can reduce migraine severity for some people\n- Helps constrict blood vessels in the brain\n\nCautions:\n- Too much caffeine can cause rebound headaches\n- Individual responses vary\n- Excessive consumption can lead to dependency\n- Not recommended for people sensitive to caffeine\n\nWhile coffee can help some people, it's not a universal solution for all headaches. If headaches persist, consult a healthcare professional.",
